definitions.definition: To make empty; to remove the contents of.
examples: to empty a well or a cistern
The cinema emptied quickly after the end of the film.
The suspected thief was requested to empty her pockets.

definitions.definition: Of a river, duct, etc: to drain or flow toward an ultimate destination.
examples: Salmon River empties on the W shore about 2 miles below Bear River.

main_definition: ( transitive , ergative ) To make empty; to remove the contents of.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) Of a river, duct, etc: to drain or flow toward an ultimate destination.
